00:17:58,376 --> 00:18:02,376
1, 2, 3, 1, 2, 3, 1!

260
00:18:02,836 --> 00:18:05,876
2, 3, 1, 2, 3, 1!

261
00:18:18,556 --> 00:18:21,036
The grandmother, Clara, where is the grandmother?

262
00:18:21,716 --> 00:18:23,716
Grandmother, grandmother!

263
00:18:24,716 --> 00:18:27,716
Grandmother, please no!

264
00:18:29,716 --> 00:18:31,716
Grandmother!

265
00:18:32,836 --> 00:18:35,836
No, don't go away!

266
00:18:35,836 --> 00:18:39,836
Grandmother, don't go away! Stay with us!

267
00:18:41,836 --> 00:18:43,836
Grandmother, Grandmother, stay here!

268
00:18:43,836 --> 00:18:48,836
Please don't go away! No, no! Grandmother!

269
00:18:48,836 --> 00:18:50,836
Heidi!

270
00:18:51,836 --> 00:18:57,836
Stay, Heidi! Go home and tell Clara that I'm very, very sorry!

271
00:18:57,836 --> 00:19:02,836
Goodbye! Come back, please!

272
00:19:02,836 --> 00:19:04,836
Goodbye, my child!

273
00:19:04,836 --> 00:19:06,836
Goodbye!

274
00:19:27,836 --> 00:19:30,836
To be continued

275
00:19:50,024 --> 00:19:52,524
It's you, Tinette. Wasn't that a wonderful party?

276
00:19:52,524 --> 00:19:53,524
It's over.

277
00:19:53,524 --> 00:19:55,524
Where are our guests?

278
00:19:55,524 --> 00:19:57,524
Mrs. Rottenmeier threw them out.

279
00:19:57,524 --> 00:19:58,524
To the front door.

280
00:19:58,524 --> 00:20:02,524
Well, at least she slipped on a poppy seed.

281
00:20:03,524 --> 00:20:07,524
You shouldn't be sad, but I really gave it to her.

282
00:20:07,524 --> 00:20:09,524
She took herself impossible in front of people.

283
00:20:09,524 --> 00:20:11,524
Completely impossible.

284
00:20:20,024 --> 00:20:24,024
Clara!

285
00:20:32,024 --> 00:20:33,024
Clara!

286
00:20:35,024 --> 00:20:36,024
Grandmother is gone.

287
00:20:36,024 --> 00:20:38,024
She's secretly gone.

288
00:20:38,024 --> 00:20:39,024
I know.

289
00:20:40,104 --> 00:20:42,104
Just like every time.

290
00:20:42,612 --> 00:20:44,612
To be continued

291
00:21:40,085 --> 00:21:43,085
This nonsense stops right away.

292
00:21:46,085 --> 00:21:48,085
Sounds good.

293
00:21:48,085 --> 00:21:53,085
I really hope that in the time with Mrs. Sesemann your good education has not
been completely lost.

294
00:21:53,085 --> 00:22:01,085
It may have been very entertaining for you all, but we probably want to go back
to behaving like decent young ladies.

295
00:22:01,085 --> 00:22:04,085
I hope you understand what I mean.

296
00:22:04,085 --> 00:22:06,085
The nobility is sitting right now.

297
00:22:06,085 --> 00:22:09,085
Well, as always, she just doesn't listen.

298
00:22:10,085 --> 00:22:12,085
That's the way it is.

299
00:22:15,829 --> 00:22:22,789
Adelheid please. You seem to have forgotten that a lady doesn't snore.

300
00:22:22,789 --> 00:22:28,849
Is good. Adelheid, what are you doing again now?

301
00:22:28,849 --> 00:22:32,989
Oh, have you forgotten that you have staff for something like that? Sebastian,

302
00:22:32,989 --> 00:22:34,489
where are you? A new spoon.

303
00:22:34,489 --> 00:22:35,829
Thank you, Sebastian.

